# {{PROJECT_NAME}} Screenshot Skill

Captures full-page PNG screenshots (1440×900 viewport) of every page listed
in `pages.json`. Script lives at `.claude/skills/screenshot-{{SLUG}}/scripts/`.

Generated by the global `screenshot-skill-init` skill. To change the page
list, edit `pages.json` directly. To change targets, edit the `TARGETS`
constant at the top of `scripts/screenshot.py`.

## Output location

```
scratch/screenshots/{target}-{YYYY-MM-DD}-{HHmm}/
```

Multiple runs per day get distinct timestamps so earlier runs are preserved.
The run label (directory basename) is printed at the end of the script output.

## Target servers

See `TARGETS` at the top of `scripts/screenshot.py`. Available: {{TARGET_NAMES}}.

## Step-by-step

### Step 1 — Determine target

Ask the user which target(s) to capture: {{TARGET_NAMES}}. If context makes it
obvious (e.g. "screenshot before deploying"), confirm rather than guess.

### Step 2 — For ddev target: confirm ddev is running

```bash
ddev status 2>/dev/null | grep -E "running|stopped" | head -3
```

If stopped, start it: `ddev start`

### Step 3 — For auth'd targets: export credentials

Any target with `auth_user_env` / `auth_pass_env` set needs those env vars
exported in the user's shell before running. The script will refuse to run if
they're missing.

### Step 4 — Run the screenshot script

Run from the **project root** so `scratch/` resolves correctly.

```bash
uv run --with playwright python3 .claude/skills/screenshot-{{SLUG}}/scripts/screenshot.py --target {{DEFAULT_TARGET}}
```

Swap `{{DEFAULT_TARGET}}` for any other configured target name.

If `uv` is not installed: `brew install uv`. Plain `python3 script.py` also
works if `playwright` is already installed in the active environment.

### Step 5 — Report back

Note the run label (the output directory basename, e.g.
`{{DEFAULT_TARGET}}-2026-04-20-1432`) and any failed pages. Tell the user:
- Which target was captured
- The run label to use when referencing these screenshots
- Number of pages captured vs failed

## Notes

- **Cache warm-up**: The script visits every page once before taking
  screenshots to prime server-side caches.
- **Self-signed certs (ddev)**: `ignore_https_errors` is applied to targets
  flagged `self_signed: true`.
- **User-agent**: A desktop Chrome UA is sent — some servers return 403 to
  default headless UAs.
- **Slow pages**: Pages that never reach `networkidle` fall back to
  `load` + 2s — usually pages with third-party embeds (donate forms etc).
- **Overwriting**: Re-running the same target on the same day creates a new
  timestamped directory.
